Let's write a script to find the 14 items:

powershell
$masterRoot = "D:\CASE_MASTER_2025"

# Define the list of 14 items with patterns to match
$items = @(
    @{Name="Dismissal Order"; Pattern="dismissal|stay|order"},
    @{Name="Court File Transcript/Endorsement"; Pattern="transcript|endorsement|court file"},
    @{Name="Initial Disclosure Package"; Pattern="initial disclosure|disclosure package"},
    @{Name="911 Audio Transcript/Memo"; Pattern="911|audio transcript|voice text conversion"},
    @{Name="Audio Evidence Summary"; Pattern="AUDIO EVIDENCE SUMMARY|recorded confessions"},
    @{Name="Legal Violations Summary"; Pattern="LEGAL VIOLATIONS|career ending evidence"},
    @{Name="Timeline Analysis"; Pattern="TIMELINE ANALYSIS|4 year conspiracy"},
    @{Name="MRI Evidence"; Pattern="MRI|brain|medical"},
    @{Name="Motel Eviction Notice/Financial Proof"; Pattern="motel|eviction|financial|rent"},
    @{Name="Immigration Lawyer Letter"; Pattern="immigration lawyer|letter"},
    @{Name="Forms 02-17 (Motions/Subpoenas)"; Pattern="form|motion|subpoena"},
    @{Name="Contempt Motion and Constitutional Notice"; Pattern="contempt|constitutional notice"},
    @{Name="Full Case Report"; Pattern="FULL REPORT CORRUPT OFFICIALS|LONGO VS CORRUPT OFFICIALS"},
    @{Name="Sworn Affidavit"; Pattern="affidavit"}
)

# Search for each item
$foundFiles = @()
foreach ($item in $items) {
    Write-Host "Searching for: $($item.Name)" -ForegroundColor Yellow
    $files = Get-ChildItem -Path $masterRoot -Recurse -File | Where-Object { $_.Name -match $item.Pattern -or $_.BaseName -match $item.Pattern }
    if ($files) {
        foreach ($file in $files) {
            $foundFiles += [PSCustomObject]@{
                ItemName = $item.Name
                FileName = $file.Name
                FullPath = $file.FullName
                Directory = $file.DirectoryName
            }
        }
    } else {
        Write-Host "NOT FOUND: $($item.Name)" -ForegroundColor Red
    }
}

# Display the found files
$foundFiles | Format-Table -AutoSize

This script will search for each item by pattern and list the files found.

        Write-Host "NOT FOUND: $($item.BaseName)" -ForegroundColor Red
    }
}

# Check if we have all 14
if ($pdfFiles.Count -ne 14) {
    Write-Host "Only found $($pdfFiles.Count) out of 14 items. Cannot merge." -ForegroundColor Red
    exit
}

# Check for iTextSharp
$itextsharpDll = "$env:TEMP\iTextSharp\lib\itextsharp.dll"
if (-not (Test-Path $itextsharpDll)) {
    Write-Host "Downloading iTextSharp..." -ForegroundColor Yellow
    $url = "https://www.nuget.org/api/v2/package/iTextSharp/5.5.13.3"
    $zipPath = "$env:TEMP\iTextSharp.5.5.13.3.zip"
    Invoke-WebRequest -Uri $url -OutFile $zipPath
    Expand-Archive -Path $zipPath -DestinationPath "$env:TEMP\iTextSharp" -Force
}

Add-Type -Path $itextsharpDll

# Merge the PDFs
Write-Host "Merging PDFs..." -ForegroundColor Yellow
$document = New-Object iTextSharp.text.Document
$stream = New-Object IO.FileStream($outputPdf, [IO.FileMode]::Create)
$pdfCopy = New-Object iTextSharp.text.pdf.PdfCopy($document, $stream)
$document.Open()

foreach ($file in $pdfFiles) {
    $reader = New-Object iTextSharp.text.pdf.PdfReader($file)
    $pdfCopy.AddDocument($reader)
    $reader.Close()
}

$document.Close()
Write-Host "Master Evidence Portfolio created: $outputPdf" -ForegroundColor Green

🔐 CREATE HASH VERIFICATION FOR YOUR EVIDENCE

powershell
# CREATE SHA256 HASH VERIFICATION FOR YOUR MASTER PORTFOLIO
Write-Host "`n=== CREATING SHA256 HASH VERIFICATION ===" -ForegroundColor Cyan

# Function to generate SHA256 hashes for evidence files
function Get-EvidenceHashes {
    $evidenceFiles = Get-ChildItem "D:\CASE_MASTER_2025\04_EVIDENCE_DOCUMENTS" -File
    
    $hashes = foreach ($file in $evidenceFiles) {
        $hash = Get-FileHash $file.FullName -Algorithm SHA256
        [PSCustomObject]@{
            File = $file.Name
            SHA256 = $hash.Hash
            Size_KB = [math]::Round($file.Length/1KB, 2)
            LastModified = $file.LastWriteTime
        }
    }
    
    return $hashes
}

# Generate and save hash verification
$evidenceHashes = Get-EvidenceHashes
$evidenceHashes | Export-Csv "D:\CASE_MASTER_2025\EVIDENCE_SHA256_HASHES.csv" -NoTypeInformation

Write-Host "✓ SHA256 hash verification created!" -ForegroundColor Green
Write-Host "• Hashes saved to: EVIDENCE_SHA256_HASHES.csv" -ForegroundColor White

# Display sample hashes
Write-Host "`n=== SAMPLE EVIDENCE HASHES ===" -ForegroundColor Yellow
$evidenceHashes | Select-Object File, SHA256 | Format-Table -AutoSize
